THE ROLE
Expand all
Job Description
Reports directly to: CRES Geography Head - MENAP ; Corporate Real Estate Services
Reports indirectly to: Head of Project Management and Design ; Corporate Real Estate Services
Direct reports: TBC
Indirect reports: Country PM, MENAP and Outsourced Service Providers as appropriate
Key Stake Holders: Head of Project Management Office
Head of Project Construction Management and Methods
Head of Project Design Solutions
CRES Geographies - Country Heads - MENAP
Hub Virtual Project Team Members
Responsible for project delivery capability related to capital projects- collect specific requirement aligning the Business investment plans with Group and Country CRES programs. Simplify standards, processes and enhance deepen team capability that improve systematic project implementation performance metrics while achieving space optimization and cost rationalization together with Hub PPT and wider RHPM network.
Responsible to manage project approvals, KPI and performance reporting - Own and manage stakeholder engagement plan connecting investment activity with CRES plans through country PM and PSC or PWGs. Manage stakeholders ensuring approval submission quality, timeliness, pipeline, WIP and coordinating annual budgets, quarterly FC and all APR activity. Establish and report premises performance against KPIs, supply and influence dashboards with stakeholders to provoke, influence and challenge issues related affordability, flexibility or life-cycle operations. Act as conduit between PDM delivery teams and PDM specialist support team.
Responsible for project Delivery - Support CRES Country PM network with resource planning, value engineering and risk assessment in rolling out core and transformational projects together with Hub PPT. Assist business to develop aligned annual premises investment plan while ensuring YoY end-to-end project execution that enables continuous improvement in premises quality (i.e. requirements, site selection, approvals, construction and FM). Provide management feedback and direction that influence Group Real Estate, Environmental and facility management technical standards suitable to geography. Ensure collaborative engagement with GS & GTO to define and deliver strategies.
Responsible for CRES standards alignment - with full understating of CRES standards and process, form and shape clear capital project investment strategy at an early stage to gain support and alignment meeting multiple stakeholder needs. Bring technical solutions and pragmatic outcomes that are in-line with objectives, affordable, global and local in operations, compliance and Brand.
Key Behaviours:
Have an outcome/ownership focus driving a cross functional and matrix team to deliver measurable KPI improvement against agreed targets within a virtual team. Includes CRES Ways of Working.
Work within established strategic imperatives that will lead to specific action plans related to premises optimization and project delivery. Working through others, provide quality analysis leading to CRES recommendations that create value propositions for the business to leverage as a competitive advantage and also bring focus to Brand opportunity within our buildings and real property.
Measures of success
* Aligned leasing programme and aligned Capital improvement programme evident at budget
* Improved KPI(s) for the property network (Africa)
* Inter-business use of standards CRES reports and information
* Introduction of controlled decision platform and identified risk evident in dashboards, PARs, reports
* CRES professional input and business strategy evident in standards and project execution plans
* Participation by invitation ; no need to force open the doors within Business or Geography forums
Authorities:
* Group CRES APR - Member
* Regional CRES APR - Chair
* Group Distribution Design Council (GDDC) - Member
* Office Design Council (ODC) - Member
How To Apply
Please apply online. To help speed up your application, please note the following:
- You will need to log in (or register if you are visiting our careers site for the first time) before you can apply for a specific role
- Some roles may require you to undertake an online talent assessment in addition to completing the application form (to facilitate this process it is preferable that you provide us with an email address as part of your contact information)
- We will ask you about your education, career history and skills and experience, it may be helpful to have this information at hand when completing your application
It usually takes 15 - 20 minutes to complete the application form; you can save your application at any time and return to complete it at your convenience.
Closing Dates
The closing date for applications is 18/05/2014. Please note all closing dates are given in Hong Kong time (GMT + 8 hours). We aim to respond to successful applicants within four weeks and will keep a record or your application in our database so that we can contact you when suitable vacancies arise in future.
Diversity & Inclusion
Standard Chartered is committed to diversity and inclusion. We believe that a work environment which embraces diversity will enable us to get the best out of the broadest spectrum of people to sustain strong business performance and competitive advantage. By building an inclusive culture, each employee can develop a sense of belonging, and have the opportunity to maximise their personal potential.
REQUIREMENTS
Knowledge, Skills & Experience
* Experience with premises and capital projects planning, leasing, design and project management
* Detail knowledge of premises costs, performance measures and standards (specifically quality)
* Effective interpersonal skills, influencing teams and diplomacy to achieve programme outcomes
* Intelligent client capability to translate between business and technical objectives
* Management capability to use statistical and data leading to focused reporting
ABOUT THE COMPANY
Standard Chartered Bank started in 1958 in UAE with its first branch in Sharjah. The Group's business gradually increased in Dubai with the opening of several branches and today, Dubai is the administrative hub of the Middle East and South Asia Region. In its 43rd year, the Bank enjoys the position of having the most extensive branch network among foreign international banks in UAE with 10 branches emirate-wide.
Standard Chartered is an international bank, focused on the established and emerging markets of Asia, Africa, the Middle East and Latin America with an extensive global network of more than 600 offices in over 50 countries. The three principal business groups are Global Markets, Personal Banking and Corporate and Institutional Banking.
In UAE, we are one of the leading banks, offering an extensive range of products and services for personal customers, local companies, multinational corporate and financial institutions.
